questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a `Spring Boot` service is failing to persist audit logs. The code looks like this:

java
@Service
public class OrderService {
    @Autowired private OrderRepository repository;

    public void placeOrder(Order order) {
        // Business logic
        repository.save(order);
        this.logTransaction(order);
    }

    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void logTransaction(Order order) {
        // Audit logging logic
    }
}

Even though `placeOrder` completes, if a subsequent failure occurs, the `logTransaction` is rolled back or never starts its own transaction.
